Male postabdomen: Sternite 5 with lateral margins rounded, converging, posterior margin with a pair of thin, incurved lobes, anterior apodeme short and broad (
Fig. 23
). Surstylus very broad, posterior edges nearly meeting medially (
Fig. 22
). Pregonite distinct, relatively large. Postgonite with lobes widely separated, anterior lobe curved anteriorly, long, rounded, posterior lobe pointed. Basiphallus with broad, very short epiphallus, short, narrow preepiphallus. Ejaculatory apodeme somewhat enlarged. Distiphallus simple, with a smooth, weakly curved dorsal tube (
Fig. 21
).
